urope@imagination.com           Accreditation  As a client-focussed organisation, Imagination seeks to conform to industry best practice while transforming business through creativity. To demonstrate our on-going commitment to the ever changing business and marketing needs of our clients, our processes and procedures are externally audited by the BSI Group to the following ISO Standards: Imagination is focussed on managing risk in all its forms, at all levels of the company and in all disciplines on each and every project. And we are committed to continuous service improvement to the benefit of clients, stakeholders, and staff.   ISO 9001:2015 Quality Management    Imagination has an established and mapped core process system to ensure the smooth running of all projects, the delivery of customer satisfaction and the building of strong client relationships. Imagination’s six stage project management process - Our Way - encompasses all the elements necessary to ensure projects are correctly managed and delivered - from the development of the initial brief through to delivery and final invoicing. Clients are encouraged at every stage to participate, review and comment on all aspects of the project.  In this way, we ensure that safeguards are in place to facilitate innovative yet practical creative solutions, focused communication and consistently high levels of client satisfaction.      ISO 14001:2015 Environmental Management    Imagination is certificated to the ISO 14001 Environmental Management standard in Europe to a level appropriate to the nature and scale of its organisation and activities with the aim of effectively managing and reducing the impact of our business processes on the environment worldwide. The Environmental Policy evidences senior management’s commitment to protecting the environment, reducing waste, meeting our contractual and compliance obligations, and working with interested parties including clients, suppliers, local authorities, local communities and our staff.      ISO 27001:2013 Information Security Management    Imagination was first certificated to the ISO 27001:2013 Information Security Management Standard in September 2016. The company’s Integrated Management System which complies with the requirements of ISO 9001 Quality Management, ISO 14001 Environmental Management and now ISO 27001 is intended to inspire confidence within Imagination that the company can articulate and demonstrate industry best practice when responding to client needs.  Certification to ISO 27001 provides assurance within the company, and to clients and partners that the confidentiality, integrity and availability of their information will be managed appropriately. It ensures that information security decisions and investments are based on risk assessment of the relevant assets. It re-enforces the company’s ongoing ability to meet contractual commitments through appropriate business continuity plans.  Imagination’s Integrated Management System takes into account business and regulatory requirements, and contractual security obligations. It is designed to raise the awareness of all employees and relevant contractors so they can identify and fulfil contractual, legislative and company specific security management responsibilities.  If you require further details, please contact our Information Security Officer.             Key Policies  Imagination is focussed on managing risk in all its forms, at all levels of the company and in all disciplines on each and every project, and we are committed to continuous service improvement to the benefit of clients, stakeholders, and staff. Please follow the links below for more details on each of our key policies.   Privacy Policy  Download PDF   Modern Slavery Policy  Download PDF   Supplier Information Security Requirements  Download PDF   Anti-Bribery Policy  Download PDF   Modern Slavery Statement  Download PDF   Environmental Policy  Download PDF  Health & Safety Policies   Europe Poli